    narr:narration """This hub catalogs the rhetorical markers and idiolects that define the aswritten.ai narrative. These phrases function as recognition handles for positioning, technical conviction, and personal style. Positioning canon is anchored by terms like [institutional knowledge at the cursor](narr:StyleObs_StockPhrase_InstitutionalKnowledge) and the [senior expert bottleneck](narr:StyleObs_StockPhrase_SeniorExpertBottleneck), while [graph-as-product](narr:StyleObs_StockPhrase) nomenclature frames the marketplace thesis. Rhetorical reframes often employ specific structures, such as the [builder-trap redefinition](narr:StyleObs_BuilderTrap) or the [optimization-not-prerequisite](narr:StyleObs_OptimizationNotPrereq) scope move. Technical-boundary idioms range from [fire-and-forget](narr:StyleObs_FeatureNotBug) to the emergent [vibe coding](narr:StyleObs_VibeCoding). The collection also captures conviction-weight markers, including [settled design decisions](narr:StyleObs_SettledDecisionMarker) and the use of [all-caps FOUNDATION](narr:StyleObs_7) to signal formal taxonomy. Personal idiolects remain distinct, from [Scarlet's 'zombie' env-var metaphor](narr:StyleObs_ZombieIdiolect) to the [signature 'Herself' sign-off](narr:StyleObs_Signature_1). Finally, structural habits—such as the [rule of three](narr:StyleObs_3) and the use of [strikethrough for deprecation](narr:StyleObs_3)—serve as typographic enactments of the underlying narrative architecture.""" ;
